Police in Eldoret are investigating circumstances that led to the death UDA MCA nominee for the Sambirir ward seat in Elgeyo Marakwet County. The nominee Mark Bowen popularly known as Sawachan died at a hospital in Eldoret on Saturday morning hours after he was found unconscious lying along the Eldoret-Uganda road near the Central Bank branch in the town. Sawachan had won the UDA primaries and was to vie for the seat in the August polls. A good Samaritan who was passing near the scene took the deceased to hospital at midnight on Friday but he succumbed hours later. He had broken legs and it was not clear how he sustained the injuries. Marakwet West MP William Kisaang who is a cousin to the deceased said they had reported to the police to follow up on the matter. Uasin Gishu police boss Ayub Gitonga said they were investigating the incident. “The deceased had injuries on his legs and head but all his items were found intact on him," Kisang said. He urged residents of the area to be calm as the matter was being investigated. “We are saddened by the loss and pray that God gives the family strength to bear the loss," Kisang said. He was also a prominent businessman in Eldoret and Senator Kipchumba Murkomen was among those who visited the family to condole with them. “It said that we have lost such a prosing leader and we join the family in mourning at this difficult time," Murkomen said. He said the deceased was a committed and active member of UDA and that he was known to always help many less fortunate people in the area. Deputy President William Ruto also sent out a message of condolence to the family. His body was taken to the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital to await a postmortem that will help to determine the cause of his death. Family members and friends met in Eldoret and expressed shock at his demise. The deceased was married and had children.